  "title": "Corporate Secretarial Manager (Central)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li>Lead and mentor junior staff, providing guidance and training to ensure team effectiveness and professional development</li><li>Assist in maintaining a portfolio of clients in Singapore companies.</li><li>Assist in drafting and updating of corporate secretarial records.</li><li>Draft and review directors’ and shareholders’ resolutions, relevant statutory forms, and supporting documents for corporate transactions (e.g., incorporation, restructuring, share allotments/transfers, strike-offs).</li><li>Liaise and coordinate with statutory bodies (such as ACRA), banks, auditors, and external business partners as needed.</li><li>Review and provide advice on compliance requirements, corporate governance practices, and corporate secretarial matters in accordance with the Singapore Companies Act and ACRA guidelines.</li><li>Prepare standard corporate documents for various company transactions.</li><li>Maintain accurate client records and manage document workflows.</li><li>Follow compliance and regulatory requirements.</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned by superiors.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum of Degree in Business Administration/Business Management and above.</li><li>At least 5 years of experience as a corporate secretary.</li><li>Qualified or part-qualified in ICSA, CSIS, or equivalent.</li><li>Familiar with the Singapore Companies Act and ACRA e-filing.</li><li>Knowledge on compliance of statutory requirements and other government legislative</li><li>Ability to prioritize work and meet deadlines.</li><li>Good written and verbal communication skills.</li><li>Proficiency in mandarin is vital for this role to deal with mandarin speaking counterparts</li></ul>",
